{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"967a6094-4cfc-4f78-9d54-14077c809283","content":"The template looks mostly well-structured but has a few issues before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation (e.g., `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`)\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `preferNameDirectory` — typically `true` for project templates\n- `description` — important for discoverability on NuGet\n- `groupIdentity` — needed if you plan multiple related templates\n\n**Other concerns:**\n- No `guids` array if the template contains any GUIDs that should be replaced\n- No `defaultName` for the project when no name is supplied\n\n**Looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, `sourceName`, and `symbols` are all valid and well-formed.\n\n**Verdict:** Not quite ready. At minimum, add a `description` field — NuGet packages without one have poor discoverability. Adding `$schema` and `preferNameDirectory: true` is also strongly recommended.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"388798e9-4c8b-49c7-ad2d-e80fa8256880","outputTokens":247,"requestId":"501E:14859A:31B8E49:3651E8C:69FBE374"},"id":"7721c44a-efc1-45d7-bd27-d015fb106aef","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:32.591Z","parentId":"7295677c-ca91-400b-972b-a9278c3b87f2"}
